channel.title: Can a 1,000 Level 3's kill 1 level 126
channel.description:
Ok so this is a very old debate on runescape forums i just wanted to know what you people think...
Level 126- No armour No Wepon Level 3's- No Armour No Wepon
my opinion is level 3's here's why
Ok if you think of it mathmaticly
1,000 level 3's out of those 1,000 only 99 of those 1,000 level 3's has to hit a "1" and the level 126 is dead so just under 1/4 of the level 3's have to hit a 1. now for the level 126 the level 126 has to hit 10,000 times but with there 1 defence would that be easy? No there's know way a level 126 would hit 10,000 times before 1,000 level 3's hit 99 times
let you decide
Debate now?

item.title: Can a 1,000 Level 3's kill 1 level 126
item.dc:creator: @xxlegitxx xxlegitxx
item.description:
@xxlegitxx wrote:

If I were a cock, I’d be far up your ass. I see no turds in my general vicinity; I am thus, not a cock. Also, having posted my fairly coherent proof no less than five times in this thread, I have reason to be slightly agitated towards anyone who says level 3’s couldn’t hit the 126. And I shall post my proof here once again because I’m a nice guy and I natural inclination towards males named Chris.

xxlegitxx:

Given the 126 kills a 3 every turn, the level 3’s will have done 500,500 attacks by the time the 126 finishes off the last one. So in order to defeat the 126, the level 3’s must deal 99 damage by, at latest, the 500,500th attack. 500,500/99 = 5056 attacks per one hp. That means they must take off 1 hp per 5056 attacks. And my point is that they would hit 1 way before the five thousandth attack, making it a sure loss for the 126.

Also, if you still choose to not believe, I’d suggest grabbing one of the 14k people with 99 defense and having a level three attack it. Or do it in Moparscape, if that can be considered accurate to any extent.
